{
  "stem": "27335.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as young as that-- and then for the harvest time, Calgary was the [INAUDIBLE] of our-- next year, 1931, we went to-- farther into-- to-- for the harvest again.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then we got acquainted with the-- with the Hungarian organization.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was much, much bigger than-- than in Edmonton.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because Calgary was a central-- there was a Drumheller-- [INAUDIBLE] the coal mines there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were 63 coal mines in Drumheller-- Drumheller [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so only work in the winter time, and in summer, all these miners came into Calgary.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The cowboy-- it was a cowboy town, and other agricultural workers.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes, yes, yes-- from the paper, it was-- it was at that time, it was twice, twice a week, the paper.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were very, very, well-- well-- well-informed, you see.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, the so-called-- the year, the international-- international Marxist movement, we all had a connection, and news-- news [INAUDIBLE] and so on, to the communist party here in Canada, in Toronto.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Well, there was no-- no problem of-- of-- of getting news first-hand.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And knew all about Hungary, and then Hitler-- definitely.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and this-- this-- organization, the leftist organization was in it up to its-- its elbows, and up to its knees.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- and-- because like-- like in Edmonton-- since you asked me, you provoked me into it-- in that area, there was a lot of Germans-- German settlers, and so on.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And later, like in 1938, already, they organized a picnic that in all Saskatchewan, we were to flow into Edmonton-- there's a huge basin there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they organized a German picnic there-- 40,000 Germans came together, you see, and they were already, 'heil Hitler,' in that picnic, in 1938.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Oh, yes, yes, yes, yes-- they had-- they had big plans.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
